<paragraph blockId="11.[227,1436,532,632]" pageId="11" pageNumber="21">
Genus of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korn" authorityYear="2002" box="[521,689,532,558]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="11" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ponticeratinae">Ponticeratinae</taxonomicName>
with extremely discoidal, subevolute to evolute conch. Often with ventrolateral grooves. Suture line with very wide external lobe, moderately high median saddle, small E2 lobe, shallow and rounded lateral lobe. Suture line formula (E2 E1 E2) L: I or (E2 E1 E2) L: U I.
</paragraph>
