<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[227,341,1221,1247]" box="[227,341,1221,1247]" pageId="11" pageNumber="21">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,1221,1247]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,1221,1247]" pageId="11" pageNumber="21">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[226,1437,1269,1442]" pageId="11" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matern" authorityYear="1929" box="[227,354,1270,1295]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" genus="Ponticeras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="11" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[227,354,1270,1295]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="21">Ponticeras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is, next to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bensaid" authorityYear="1974" box="[483,723,1269,1295]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" genus="Pseudoprobeloceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="11" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[483,723,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="21">Pseudoprobeloceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the stratigraphically oldest genus of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1206,1433,1269,1295]" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Gephuroceratoidea">Gephuroceratoidea</taxonomicName>
. The two genera mainly differ in the shape of the external lobe; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bensaid" authorityYear="1974" box="[991,1231,1306,1332]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" genus="Pseudoprobeloceras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="11" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[991,1231,1306,1332]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="21">Pseudoprobeloceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is quite narrow with a low median saddle and in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matern" authorityYear="1929" box="[607,734,1343,1368]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" genus="Ponticeras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="11" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[607,734,1343,1368]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="21">Ponticeras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is very broad with a quite high median saddle. The genera of the closely related family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frech" authorityYear="1897" box="[562,771,1379,1405]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Gephuroceratidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="11" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Gephuroceratidae</taxonomicName>
differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matern" authorityYear="1929" box="[915,1042,1380,1405]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Ponticeratidae" genus="Ponticeras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="11" pageNumber="21" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[915,1042,1380,1405]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="21">Ponticeras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the acute lateral lobe, which is rounded in 
